  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Computers For Schools Burundi&apos;s goal is to close the digital gap in the education of Burundi&apos;s children. Two schools in Burundi, one primary and the other secondary will be equipped with ICT labs of 43 computers connected to the Internet. Students will learn ICT, coding, research, and digital entrepreneurship. The Project will also train 40 instructors to teach the ICT curriculum to 1,560 students this will help prepare Burundian youth to compete in the global economy&apos;s job markets.</narrative>
  </description>
